03:02.200 --> 03:05.328
I'm going for a cup of tea.
Do you want one?

03:06.738 --> 03:10.174
<i>- Do you want a cup of tea, Withnail?
- No.</i>

03:59.454 --> 04:02.320
<i>Thirteen million
Londoners have to wake up to this.</i>

04:02.423 --> 04:05.324
<i>The murder and all-bran
and rape?</i>

04:05.426 --> 04:08.918
<i>And I'm sitting in this bloody shack,
and I can't cope with Withnail.</i>

04:09.029 --> 04:11.088
<i>I must be out of my mind.</i>

04:11.198 --> 04:14.258
<i>I must go home at once and
discuss his problems in depth.</i>

04:17.070 --> 04:19.732
I have some extremely
distressing news.

04:19.839 --> 04:22.831
<i>I don't want to hear it.
I don't want to hear anything.</i>

04:24.444 --> 04:28.039
<i>My God, it's a nightmare,
let me tell you. It's a nightmare.</i>

04:28.147 --> 04:31.139
We've just run out of wine.
What are we gonna do about it?

04:31.250 --> 04:33.740
<i>I don't know.
I don't know.</i>

04:33.852 --> 04:36.878
Oh, God!
I don't feel good.

04:36.989 --> 04:41.187
My thumbs have gone weird!

04:41.293 --> 04:44.558
I'm in the middle
of a bloody overdose.

04:44.663 --> 04:47.632
Oh, God!

04:47.733 --> 04:50.792
My heart's beating
like a fucked clock!

04:50.901 --> 04:53.335
I feel dreadful.
I feel really dreadful.

04:53.437 --> 04:55.803
So do I.
So does everybody.

04:55.906 --> 04:57.931
Look at my tongue.

04:58.042 --> 05:00.510
Gray yellow sock.

05:00.611 --> 05:03.341
Sit down, for Christ's sake.
What's the matter with you?

05:04.815 --> 05:07.476
Eat some sugar.

05:07.584 --> 05:10.951
Listen to this.
"Curse of the supermen.

05:11.054 --> 05:14.854
"'I took drugs to win medal,'
says top athleteJeff Wode.

05:14.958 --> 05:17.927
<i>- Where's the coffee?
- "In a world exclusive interview,</i>

05:18.028 --> 05:22.259
<i>"33-year-old shot putterJeff Wode,
who weighs 317 pounds,</i>

05:22.364 --> 05:25.959
<i>"admitted taking massive doses
of anabolic steroids,</i>

05:26.068 --> 05:28.366
"drugs banned in sport.

05:28.470 --> 05:31.598
"'He used to get in bad tempers,'
says his wife.

05:31.707 --> 05:34.540
"'He used to pick on me.
But now he's stopped,

05:34.643 --> 05:37.942
he's much better in our sex
life and in our general life. "'

05:38.046 --> 05:42.847
Jesus Christ!
This huge, thatched head...

05:42.950 --> 05:47.512
with its earlobes and cannonball
is not considered sane.

05:47.622 --> 05:49.920
"Jeff Wode is feeling better...

05:50.024 --> 05:54.551
and is now prepared to step back into
society and start tossing his orb about. "

05:54.661 --> 05:57.027
Look at him!
Look at Jeff Wode!

05:57.130 --> 06:00.065
His head must weigh
50 pounds on its own.

06:01.501 --> 06:04.095
Imagine the size of his balls.

06:05.572 --> 06:08.507
Imagine getting into a fight
with the fucker.

06:08.608 --> 06:10.542
Please, I don't feel good.

06:10.644 --> 06:14.636
That's what you'd say.
But that wouldn't wash with Jeff.

06:14.747 --> 06:18.774
No. He'd like a bit of pleading.
Adds spice to it.

06:18.884 --> 06:24.049
In fact, he'd probably tell you
what he was gonna do before he did it.

06:25.558 --> 06:27.923
"I'm gonna pull your head off. "

06:28.026 --> 06:30.688
"No, please don't pull my head off. "

06:30.795 --> 06:34.891
"I'm gonna pull your head off
because I don't like your head. "

06:39.003 --> 06:42.564
Have you got soup?
Why didn't I get any soup?

06:42.674 --> 06:44.641
Coffee.

06:44.741 --> 06:46.902
Why don't you use a cup
like any other human being?

06:47.010 --> 06:49.808
Why don't you wash up occasionally
like any other human being?

06:49.913 --> 06:53.679
How dare you!
How dare you!

06:53.784 --> 06:56.252
How dare you
call me inhumane!

06:56.353 --> 06:59.345
I didn't call you inhumane.
You merely imagined it. Calm down.

06:59.456 --> 07:02.288
Right, you fucker.
I'm gonna do the washing up.

07:02.391 --> 07:05.554
No, no, you can't.
It's impossible, I swear.

07:05.661 --> 07:08.391
I've looked into it.
Listen to me! Listen to me!

07:08.498 --> 07:11.331
There are things in there.
There's a tea bag growing.

07:11.434 --> 07:14.699
You haven't slept in 60 hours.
You're in no state to tackle it.

07:14.804 --> 07:17.271
Wait till the morning.
We'll go in together.

07:17.372 --> 07:20.000
This is the morning!
Stand aside!

07:20.108 --> 07:24.067
You don't understand! I think
there may be something living in there.

07:24.179 --> 07:26.443
I think there may be
something alive.

07:26.548 --> 07:29.312
- What do you mean? A rat?
- It's possible.

07:29.417 --> 07:32.477
Then the fucker
will rue the day.

07:34.622 --> 07:39.059
Oh, Christ Almighty!
A sinew in nicotine base.

07:39.160 --> 07:42.618
Keep back, keep back.
The entire sink's gone rotten.

07:42.730 --> 07:44.630
I don't know what's in here.

07:44.732 --> 07:48.862
I told you, you've been bitten!

07:48.969 --> 07:51.698
Burnt! Burnt!
The fucking kettle's on fire!

07:51.804 --> 07:54.272
- There's something floating up.
- Fork it!

07:54.374 --> 07:57.866
- L-I-I don't...
- You must! You must!

07:57.977 --> 08:02.073
<i>The poop will boil through the glaze. We'll
never be able to use our dinner service again.</i>

08:02.182 --> 08:04.582
Here. Get it with the pliers.

08:04.684 --> 08:07.083
<i>No, no. No, no.
Give me the gloves.</i>

08:07.186 --> 08:09.882
That's right.
Put on the gloves.

08:09.988 --> 08:12.889
Don't attempt anything
without the gloves.

08:16.261 --> 08:19.162
- Ugh.
- What is it? What have you found?

08:19.264 --> 08:21.892
Matter.

08:21.999 --> 08:24.490
Matter?
Where's it coming from?

08:24.602 --> 08:27.594
Don't look.
I'm dealing with it.

08:29.674 --> 08:32.039
I think we've been
in here too long.

08:32.143 --> 08:35.772
I feel unusual.
I think we should go outside.

08:40.850 --> 08:43.784
This is ridiculous.
Look at me.

08:43.886 --> 08:47.379
I'm 30 in a month, and I've got
a sole flapping off my shoe.

08:47.490 --> 08:50.482
It will get better.
It has to.

08:50.594 --> 08:53.529
Easy for you to say, lovey.
You've had an audition.

08:53.630 --> 08:56.097
Why can't I have an audition?

08:56.198 --> 09:00.897
It's ridiculous. I've been
to drama school. I'm good-looking.

09:01.003 --> 09:05.099
I tell you, I've a fuck sight more talent
than half the rubbish that gets on television.

09:05.207 --> 09:07.300
Why can't I get on television?

09:07.409 --> 09:09.639
I don't know.
It'll happen.

09:09.745 --> 09:12.304
Will it?
That's what you say.

09:12.413 --> 09:16.008
The only program I'm likely to get on
is the fucking news.

09:16.117 --> 09:18.585
I tell you, I can't take
much more of this.

09:18.686 --> 09:21.120
- I'm gonna crack.
- I'm in the same boat.

09:21.222 --> 09:23.122
Yeah, yeah.

09:23.224 --> 09:25.818
I feel as sick as a pike.

09:25.927 --> 09:28.053
I'm gonna have to sit down.

09:33.233 --> 09:36.327
You know what we should do?

09:36.436 --> 09:39.064
I say, you know
what we should do?

09:39.172 --> 09:42.164
How can I possibly know
what we should do?

09:42.276 --> 09:45.802
- What should we do?
- Get out of it for a while.

09:45.911 --> 09:48.675
Get into the countryside,
rejuvenate.

09:48.781 --> 09:52.808
Rejuvenate? I'm in a park,
and I'm practically dead.

09:52.918 --> 09:55.819
What good's the countryside?

09:55.921 --> 10:00.085
- What time is it?
- It's 8:00.

10:00.192 --> 10:04.594
Four hours till opening time.
God help us.

10:04.696 --> 10:07.096
Have we got any embrocation?

10:09.067 --> 10:11.535
- What for?
- To rub on us, you fool.

10:11.636 --> 10:14.730
We can cover ourselves in Deep Heat
and get up against the radiator,

10:14.839 --> 10:17.306
keep ourselves alive till 12:00.

10:19.109 --> 10:21.543
Jesus, look at that!

10:21.645 --> 10:24.443
Apart from a raw potato,
that's the only solid...

10:24.548 --> 10:27.676
to have passed my lips
in the last 60 hours.

10:27.785 --> 10:30.185
I must be ill.

10:32.456 --> 10:36.289
<i>Even a stopped clock
gives the right time twice a day.</i>

10:37.794 --> 10:41.753
<i>And for once, I'm inclined to
believe that Withnail is right.</i>

10:41.864 --> 10:46.301
<i>We are, indeed, drifting
into the arena of the unwell,</i>

10:48.137 --> 10:51.128
<i>making an enemy
of our own future.</i>

10:51.239 --> 10:54.208
<i>What we need is harmony,</i>

10:54.309 --> 10:57.403
<i>fresh air, stuff like that.</i>

10:57.512 --> 11:01.004
Wasn't much in the tube.
Nothing left for you.

11:01.116 --> 11:04.415
<i>Why don't you ask your father
for some money?</i>

11:04.519 --> 11:07.487
If we had some money,
we could go away.

11:07.588 --> 11:11.251
Why don't you ask your father?
How can it be so cold in here?

11:11.359 --> 11:13.691
Like Greenland in here.

11:15.463 --> 11:19.923
We've got to get some booze. It's
the only solution for this intense cold.

11:20.034 --> 11:24.129
Something's got to be done.
We can't go on like this!

11:24.237 --> 11:28.435
I'm a trained actor
reduced to the status of a bum!

11:28.541 --> 11:33.240
I mean, look at us! Nothing that reasonable
members of society demand as their rights!

11:33.346 --> 11:36.577
No fridges, no televisions,
no phones!

11:36.683 --> 11:39.014
Much more of this, I'm gonna
apply for Meals On Wheels.

11:39.118 --> 11:43.020
- What happened to your cigar commercial?
- That's what I want to know.

11:43.122 --> 11:46.319
What happened to my agent?
Bastard must have died.

11:46.425 --> 11:48.325
<i>September. Bad patch.</i>

11:48.427 --> 11:51.555
Rubbish. I haven't seen Gielgud
down the Labor Exchange.

11:51.663 --> 11:53.563
Why doesn't he retire?

11:53.665 --> 11:56.565
Oh, look at this little bastard!

11:56.667 --> 12:00.000
"Boy lands plum role
for top Italian director. "

12:00.104 --> 12:04.165
'Course he does. Probably
on a tenner a day, and I know what for.

12:04.275 --> 12:08.109
Two pound ten a tit,
and a fiver for his arse.

12:10.815 --> 12:13.612
- Have you been at the controls?
- What are you talking about?

12:13.717 --> 12:16.379
The thermostats!
What have you done to them?

12:16.486 --> 12:19.649
<i>- I haven't touched them.
- Then why has my head gone numb?</i>

12:19.756 --> 12:22.247
I must have some booze.

12:22.359 --> 12:25.089
I demand to have some booze!

12:27.230 --> 12:29.959
- I wouldn't drink that if I was you.
- Why not?

12:30.065 --> 12:31.965
Because I don't advise it.

12:32.067 --> 12:34.968
Even the wankers on the site wouldn't
drink that. That's worse than meths.

12:35.070 --> 12:38.039
Nonsense. This is a far
superior drink to meths.

12:38.140 --> 12:41.007
Wankers don't drink it
because they can't afford it.

12:45.380 --> 12:48.349
Have we got any more?

12:48.450 --> 12:51.180
Liar!
What's in your toolbox?

12:51.286 --> 12:53.345
No, we have nothing.
Sit down.

12:53.455 --> 12:55.855
Liar!
You've got antifreeze.

12:55.957 --> 12:58.858
You bloody fool.
You should never mix your drinks!

13:07.734 --> 13:11.636
All right, this is the plan.
We'll get in there and get wrecked.

13:11.738 --> 13:15.674
Then we'll eat a pork pie. Then we'll
drop a couple of Surmontil 50s each.

13:15.776 --> 13:19.211
Means we'll miss out Monday
but come up smiling Tuesday morning.

13:19.312 --> 13:22.713
- What's that appalling smell?
- Perfume on my boots.

13:22.815 --> 13:25.875
I had to scrub them
with essence of petunia.

13:33.125 --> 13:37.185
Two large gins, two pints of cider,
ice in the cider.

13:37.295 --> 13:39.855
If my father was loaded,
I'd ask him for some money.

13:39.965 --> 13:42.729
If your father was my
father, you wouldn't get it.

13:42.834 --> 13:45.234
- Here you are, lads.
- Chin-chin.

13:49.007 --> 13:50.906
Ugh!

13:52.443 --> 13:55.071
What about what's-his-name?

13:55.179 --> 13:58.512
- What about him?
- Why don't you give him a call?

13:58.616 --> 14:02.052
- What for?
- Ask him about his house.

14:02.152 --> 14:05.246
You want me to call what's-his-name
and ask him about his house?

14:05.356 --> 14:08.688
- Why not?
- All right. What's his number?

14:08.791 --> 14:11.453
I have no idea.
I've never met him.

14:11.561 --> 14:14.462
Well, neither have I.
Who the fuck are you talking about?

14:14.564 --> 14:16.896
Your relative with the house
in the country.

14:17.000 --> 14:19.662
- Monty? Uncle Monty?
- Same. That's the one.

14:19.769 --> 14:22.738
Get theJag fixed up,
spend a week in the country.

14:22.838 --> 14:26.638
All right. Give us a tanner,
and I'll give him a bell.

14:26.742 --> 14:31.236
Here. Get a couple more.
I'm going for a slash.

14:38.186 --> 14:40.085
Ponce.

14:43.057 --> 14:45.753
<i>I could hardly
piss straight with fear.</i>

14:45.860 --> 14:49.421
<i>A man with three-quarters of an inch
of brain had taken a dislike to me.</i>

14:49.530 --> 14:53.933
<i>What have I done to offend him? I don't
consciously offend big men like this.</i>

14:54.035 --> 14:56.935
<i>And this one has a definite
imbalance of hormone in him.</i>

14:57.037 --> 15:00.165
<i>Get any more masculine than him,
you'd have to live up a tree.</i>

15:00.273 --> 15:03.504
<i>"I fuck arses. "
Who fucks arses?</i>

15:03.610 --> 15:06.306
<i>Maybe he fucks arses.</i>

15:06.413 --> 15:09.541
<i>Maybe he's written this in some
moment of drunken sincerity?</i>

15:09.649 --> 15:12.116
<i>I'm in considerable
danger in here.</i>

15:12.217 --> 15:14.208
<i>I must get out of here at once.</i>

15:18.557 --> 15:20.718
Perfumed ponce!

15:22.595 --> 15:25.826
You'll be pleased to hear
Monty's invited us for drinks.

15:25.931 --> 15:28.126
Balls to Monty.
We're getting out.

15:28.233 --> 15:31.360
Balls to Monty? I already spent
an hour flattering the bugger.

15:31.469 --> 15:35.405
There's a man over there doesn't like
the perfume. A big one. Don't look.

15:35.506 --> 15:38.236
We're in danger.
We've got to get out.

15:38.343 --> 15:42.370
- What are you talking about?
- I've been called a ponce.

15:42.480 --> 15:45.607
What fucker said that?

15:51.154 --> 15:54.123
I called him a ponce,

15:54.224 --> 15:56.590
and now I'm calling you one.

15:56.693 --> 15:58.820
Ponce!

15:58.929 --> 16:01.260
Would you like a drink?

16:01.364 --> 16:03.389
What's your name? McFuck?

16:04.767 --> 16:08.328
I have a heart condition.
I have a heart condition.

16:08.437 --> 16:11.167
If you hit me, it's murder.

16:11.273 --> 16:13.969
I'll murder the pair of yous!

16:14.076 --> 16:16.772
My wife is having a baby.

16:16.879 --> 16:21.406
<i>Listen, I don't know what my...
acquaintance did to upset you,</i>

16:21.516 --> 16:24.041
but it's nothing to do with me.

16:24.152 --> 16:26.780
I suggest you both go outside...

16:26.888 --> 16:29.652
and discuss it sensibly
in the street.

16:32.327 --> 16:34.226
Out of my way!

16:39.967 --> 16:42.959
<i>Speed is like
a dozen transatlantic flights...</i>

16:43.070 --> 16:45.436
<i>without ever
getting off the plane.</i>

16:45.539 --> 16:49.635
<i>Time change.
You lose. You gain.</i>

16:49.743 --> 16:53.769
<i>Makes no difference, so long
as you keep taking the pills.</i>

16:53.880 --> 16:56.713
<i>But sooner or later,
you gotta get out...</i>

16:56.816 --> 16:58.943
<i>because it's crashing,</i>

16:59.052 --> 17:02.044
<i>and all at once
those frozen hours...</i>

17:02.155 --> 17:04.782
<i>melt through
the nervous system...</i>

17:04.891 --> 17:08.053
<i>and seep out the pores.</i>

17:09.361 --> 17:12.558
Bastards! Just to suck...

17:12.664 --> 17:16.122
some miserable cheap cigar,
and the bastards won't see me.

17:18.670 --> 17:20.637
Why are we having lunch in here?

17:20.739 --> 17:22.730
It's dinner, and Danny's here.

17:22.840 --> 17:24.740
Danny?
How did he get in?

17:24.842 --> 17:27.606
I let him in this morning.
He lost one of his clogs.

17:27.712 --> 17:30.340
He's come in because
of this perpetual cold.

17:30.448 --> 17:33.281
Oh, I hope
tobacco sales plummet.

17:33.384 --> 17:37.320
I've got your saveloy.
Here. I don't want it.

17:37.421 --> 17:40.184
Then stick it in a soap tray
and save it for later.

17:40.290 --> 17:42.952
Don't vent spleen on me!
I'm in the same boat!

17:43.059 --> 17:45.892
Stop saying that!
You're not in the same boat.

17:45.995 --> 17:50.432
The only thing you're in that
I have been in is this fucking bath!

17:52.702 --> 17:56.933
<i>Danny's here.
Headhunter to his friends.</i>

17:57.039 --> 18:00.941
<i>Headhunter to everybody.
He doesn't have any friends.</i>

18:01.043 --> 18:03.773
<i>The only people
he converses with...</i>

18:03.879 --> 18:06.780
<i>are his clients
and occasionally the police.</i>

18:06.882 --> 18:11.785
<i>The purveyor of rare herbs and
prescribed chemicals is back.</i>

18:11.887 --> 18:14.912
<i>Will we never be set free?</i>

18:19.560 --> 18:23.087
- Danny.
- You're looking very beautiful, man.

18:23.197 --> 18:25.097
Have you been away?

18:25.199 --> 18:29.259
St. Peter preached the epistles
to the apostles looking like that.

18:29.369 --> 18:31.701
Have you got any food?

18:31.805 --> 18:35.206
Mmm. As a matter of fact,
I got a saveloy.

18:35.308 --> 18:38.175
How much is it?

18:38.278 --> 18:40.473
You can have it for nothing.

18:40.580 --> 18:43.640
- I see you're wearing a suit.
- What's it got to do with you?

18:43.750 --> 18:47.981
<i>No need to get uptight, man.
I was merely making an observation.</i>

18:48.087 --> 18:52.615
<i>I happened to be looking for a suit
for the Coalman two weeks ago.</i>

18:52.725 --> 18:55.956
For reasons I can't really
discuss with you...

18:56.061 --> 18:58.655
the Coalman
had to go toJamaica.

18:58.764 --> 19:01.528
Got busted coming back
through Heathrow.

19:04.636 --> 19:06.536
Had a weight under his fez.

19:06.638 --> 19:10.768
<i>We worked out, it would be very handy
karma for him to get hold of a suit.</i>

19:10.875 --> 19:14.242
But he's a very low-temperature
spade, the Coalman.

19:14.345 --> 19:17.314
Goes into court
in his caftan and a bell.

19:17.415 --> 19:21.350
This doesn't go down at all well.

19:21.451 --> 19:25.012
They can handle the caftan,
but they can't handle the bell.

19:25.122 --> 19:28.683
So there's this judge sitting there
in the cape like fucking Batman...

19:28.792 --> 19:32.353
<i>- with this really rather
far-out looking hat... - Wig.</i>

19:32.462 --> 19:36.522
<i>No, man. This was more
like a long white hat.</i>

19:36.632 --> 19:39.157
So he looks at the Coalman
and says,

19:39.268 --> 19:42.863
"What's all this? This is a court,
man. This ain't fancy dress. "

19:42.972 --> 19:45.668
And the Coalman
looks at him and says,

19:45.775 --> 19:48.801
"You think you look normal,
Your Honor?"

19:48.911 --> 19:51.936
Cunt give him two years.

19:53.949 --> 19:57.009
I'm afraid I can't offer
you gentlemen anything.

19:57.118 --> 19:59.848
That's all right, Danny.
We decided to lay off for a bit.

19:59.955 --> 20:03.721
That's what I thought. Except
for personal use, I concur with you.

20:03.825 --> 20:08.227
As a matter of fact, I'm thinking
of retiring and going into business.

20:08.329 --> 20:10.820
Doing what?

20:10.931 --> 20:14.162
<i>- The toy industry.
- I thought you were in the bottle industry.</i>

20:14.268 --> 20:18.432
No, man. That's a sideline.
You can have that.

20:18.539 --> 20:21.269
Instructions are included.

20:21.375 --> 20:25.538
Yeah, my partner's got a really
good idea for making dolls.

20:25.645 --> 20:30.207
His name's Presuming Ed.
His sister give him the idea.

20:30.316 --> 20:33.012
She got a doll on Christmas
what pisses itself.

20:33.119 --> 20:36.555
- Really?
- Yeah, and you gotta change its drawers for it.

20:36.656 --> 20:39.682
It's horrible, really.
But they like that, little girls.

20:39.792 --> 20:42.692
So we're gonna make one
that shits itself as well.

20:42.794 --> 20:45.388
- Shits itself?
- He's an expert.

20:45.497 --> 20:48.261
He's building the prototype now.

20:51.036 --> 20:53.197
Why is he behaving so uptightly?

20:53.305 --> 20:57.263
Because a gang of cheeroot vendors
considered a haircut beyond my abilities.

20:57.375 --> 21:00.276
I don't advise a haircut, man.

21:00.378 --> 21:03.541
All hairdressers are
in the employment of the government.

21:03.648 --> 21:05.809
Hair are your aerials.

21:05.917 --> 21:08.385
They pick up signals
from the cosmos...

21:08.486 --> 21:11.284
and transmit them
directly into the brain.

21:11.389 --> 21:14.516
This is the reason
bald-headed men are uptight.

21:14.624 --> 21:16.956
What absolute twaddle.

21:18.395 --> 21:20.295
- Has he just been busted?
- No.

21:20.397 --> 21:22.627
Then why is he wearing
that old suit?

21:22.732 --> 21:26.793
Old suit? This suit
was cut by Hawke's of Savile Row.

21:26.903 --> 21:30.861
Just because the best tailoring you've ever seen is
above your fucking appendix doesn't mean anything!

21:30.973 --> 21:33.464
Don't get uptight with me, man.

21:33.575 --> 21:38.103
'Cause if you do, I'll have to
give you a dose of medicine.

21:38.213 --> 21:42.309
And if I spike you, you'll know
you've been spoken to.

21:42.418 --> 21:45.148
You wouldn't spike me.
You're too mean.

21:45.254 --> 21:48.154
Besides, there's nothing
invented I couldn't take.

21:48.256 --> 21:53.091
If I medicined you, you'd think
a brain tumor was a birthday present.

21:54.929 --> 21:58.023
I could take double
anything you could.

21:59.934 --> 22:03.334
Very, very foolish words, man.

22:03.437 --> 22:05.837
He's right, Withnail.
Look at him.

22:05.939 --> 22:08.840
His mechanism's gone. He's had
more drugs than you've had hot dinners.

22:08.942 --> 22:11.376
I'm not having this
shag sack insulting me.

22:11.478 --> 22:13.673
Let him get his drugs out.

22:13.780 --> 22:17.648
This doll
is extremely dangerous.

22:19.485 --> 22:23.421
It has voodoo qualities.

22:32.465 --> 22:38.130
Trade,
"Phenodihydrochrolide benzorex. "

22:38.236 --> 22:41.535
Street, "the embalmer. "

22:41.639 --> 22:43.869
Balls! I'll swallow it
and run a mile.

22:43.975 --> 22:48.674
Cool your boots, man.
This pill's valued at two quid.

22:48.780 --> 22:51.680
- Two quid? You're out of your mind.
- That's sense, Withnail.

22:51.782 --> 22:55.309
You can stuff it up your arse for nothing
and fuck off while you're doing it!

22:57.821 --> 23:02.315
<i>No need to insult me, man.
I was leaving anyway.</i>

23:05.662 --> 23:08.824
Have either of you got shoes?

23:34.356 --> 23:36.824
Monty's car.

23:45.366 --> 23:48.358
Oh, hello! Come in.

23:56.444 --> 24:00.140
Sit down, do.
Would you like a drink?

24:00.246 --> 24:02.339
- Sherry.
- Sherry.

24:05.452 --> 24:07.352
- Sherry?
- Sherry.

24:07.454 --> 24:09.354
Sherry.

24:13.392 --> 24:15.952
Do you like vegetables?

24:16.061 --> 24:18.791
I've always been fond
of root crops,

24:18.897 --> 24:21.422
but I only started
to grow last summer.

24:21.533 --> 24:25.128
I happen to think the cauliflower
more beautiful than the rose.

24:25.237 --> 24:27.137
Chin-chin.

24:27.239 --> 24:29.638
- Do you grow?
- Geraniums.

24:29.740 --> 24:31.833
Little traitors.

24:31.943 --> 24:35.174
I think the carrot infinitely
more fascinating than the geranium.

24:35.279 --> 24:38.737
Mmm. The carrot has mystery.

24:38.850 --> 24:41.876
Flowers are essentially tarts,

24:41.986 --> 24:45.012
prostitutes for the bees.

24:46.423 --> 24:49.483
<i>There is, you will agree,
a certain "je ne sai quoi,"</i>

24:49.593 --> 24:53.256
something very special
about a firm, young carrot.

24:53.363 --> 24:55.490
Hmm, excuse me.

24:55.599 --> 24:59.160
Do help yourselves to another drink.

24:59.269 --> 25:01.737
What's all this?
The man's mad.

25:01.838 --> 25:04.397
- Eccentric.
- Eccentric? He's insane!

25:04.507 --> 25:07.101
Not only that,
he's a raving homosexual.

25:09.211 --> 25:11.475
<i>You beastly little parasite!
How dare you?</i>

25:11.580 --> 25:14.344
You little thug!
How dare you!

25:16.986 --> 25:19.545
Beastly, ungrateful little swine!

25:19.654 --> 25:23.385
- Shall I get you a drink?
- Yes, yes, yes, please, dear boy.

25:23.491 --> 25:26.051
You can prepare me a small
rhesus-negative Bloody Mary.

25:26.161 --> 25:30.291
You must tell me all the news. I haven't
seen you since you finished your last show.

25:30.398 --> 25:33.196
Rather busy, Uncle.
TV and stuff.

25:33.301 --> 25:36.599
My agent's attempting to edge me
towards Royal Shakespeare Company again.

25:36.703 --> 25:40.605
<i>- Oh, splendid.
- And he's just had an audition for rep.</i>

25:40.707 --> 25:43.870
Oh, splendid!
So you're a Thespian too?

25:47.314 --> 25:49.305
Monty used to act.

25:49.416 --> 25:51.316
One hardly says that.

25:51.418 --> 25:54.978
I cracked the boards in my youth,
but I never really had it in my blood.

25:55.087 --> 25:57.647
And that's what's
so essential, isn't it?

25:57.757 --> 26:00.191
The theatrical zeal in the veins.

26:00.293 --> 26:04.354
Alas, I have little more
than vintage wine and memories.

26:08.667 --> 26:12.398
It is the most shattering experience
of a young man's life...

26:12.504 --> 26:16.406
when one morning he awakes
and quite reasonably says to himself,

26:16.508 --> 26:21.969
"I will never play the Dane. "

26:22.080 --> 26:25.242
When that moment comes,

26:25.349 --> 26:28.807
one's ambition ceases.

26:31.188 --> 26:33.679
Don't you agree?

26:33.791 --> 26:37.591
- It's a part I intend to play, Uncle.
- And you'll be marvelous.

26:37.695 --> 26:39.993
Marvelous.

26:41.397 --> 26:43.957
"It's gone.

26:44.067 --> 26:47.264
<i>"We do it wrong,
being so ma'jestical...</i>

26:47.370 --> 26:50.100
to offer it
the show of violence. "

26:50.206 --> 26:53.300
Let's go. He's a madman.

26:53.409 --> 26:56.173
Any minute now, he's gonna rush out
and get into his tights.

26:56.279 --> 27:00.112
- Okay, okay. Any minute.
- The house or out.

27:02.050 --> 27:04.245
Could I have a word
with you, Monty?

27:04.353 --> 27:07.288
Oh, forgive me, dear boy.
Forgive me.

27:07.389 --> 27:10.449
<i>I was allowing memory
to have the better of me.</i>

27:10.559 --> 27:13.460
<i>Shall I get you a topper?</i>

27:22.403 --> 27:25.964
Indeed, I remember my first agent.

27:26.073 --> 27:28.200
Raymond Duck.

27:30.043 --> 27:33.035
He was a dreadful little Israelite.

27:33.146 --> 27:36.115
Four floors up
on the Charing Cross Road,

27:36.216 --> 27:39.014
and never a job
at the top of them.

27:40.854 --> 27:43.652
I'm told you're a writer too.

27:45.592 --> 27:48.082
<i>Do you write poems?</i>

27:48.193 --> 27:52.152
No. I wish I could.
It's just thoughts, really.

27:53.866 --> 27:56.334
- Are you published?
- Oh, no.

27:56.435 --> 27:58.665
Where did you school?

27:58.771 --> 28:01.399
He went to the other place, Monty.

28:01.507 --> 28:04.737
Oh, you went to Eton?

28:04.842 --> 28:07.538
Get that damned little
swine out of here!

28:09.647 --> 28:13.447
It's trying to get itself in with you.
It's trying for even more advantage.

28:13.551 --> 28:15.712
It's obsessed with its gut.
It's like a bloody rugby ball now.

28:15.820 --> 28:19.118
- It will die! It will die!
- Monty. Monty.

28:19.222 --> 28:22.020
No, no, dear boy.
You must leave.

28:22.125 --> 28:24.491
Yet again, that oaf
has destroyed my day.

28:24.594 --> 28:27.620
Listen, Monty. Could I just have
a quick word with you? In private?

28:27.731 --> 28:29.892
Oh... very well.

28:41.377 --> 28:44.369
- Good night, my dears.
- Good night, Monty.

28:44.480 --> 28:47.938
What's all this going off in private
business? Why did you tell him I went to Eton?

28:48.050 --> 28:50.883
Because it wouldn't
have helped if I hadn't.

28:50.986 --> 28:54.216
I'm just trying to establish you
in some sort of context he'd understand.

28:54.322 --> 28:58.019
- What do you mean by that?
- I mean, free to those who can afford it.

28:58.126 --> 29:00.890
Very expensive
to those that can't.

29:08.602 --> 29:12.197
<i>"All Along the Watchtower"]</i>

29:45.137 --> 29:49.301
- Scrubbers!
- Up yours, Granddad!

29:49.408 --> 29:52.935
- Scrubbers! Scrubbers!
- Shut up!

29:53.044 --> 29:56.241
Little tarts.
They love it.

29:56.348 --> 29:59.339
I'm trying to drive this thing
as quietly as possible.

29:59.450 --> 30:03.216
If you don't shut up,
we'll get stopped by the police.

30:03.320 --> 30:06.483
<i>- Give me the bottle.
- Look at that. Look at that.</i>

30:06.590 --> 30:09.821
"Accident black spot. "
These aren't accidents!

30:09.927 --> 30:13.419
They're throwing themselves
into the road! Gladly!

30:13.531 --> 30:17.728
Throwing themselves into the road
to escape all this hideousness!

30:17.834 --> 30:20.701
<i>Throw yourself
into the road, darling!</i>

30:20.804 --> 30:23.364
You haven't got a chance!

31:00.475 --> 31:04.103
At some point or another,
I want to stop and get hold of a child.

31:04.211 --> 31:06.111
What do you want a child for?

31:06.213 --> 31:08.340
To tutor it in the ways
of righteousness...

31:08.448 --> 31:10.746
and procure some
uncontaminated urine.

31:10.851 --> 31:15.185
This is a device enabling the drunken
driver to operate in absolute safety.

31:15.288 --> 31:20.190
You fill this with piss,
take this pipe down the trouser...

31:20.292 --> 31:24.456
and cellotape this valve
to the end of the old chap.

31:24.563 --> 31:28.431
Then you get horribly drunk,
and they can't fucking touch you.

31:28.534 --> 31:31.526
According
to these instructions,

31:31.637 --> 31:34.697
you refuse everything
but a urine sample.

31:34.807 --> 31:37.536
You undo your valve...

31:37.642 --> 31:41.237
and give 'em a dose
of unadulterated child's piss,

31:41.346 --> 31:44.372
and they have to give you
your keys back.

31:44.482 --> 31:48.578
Danny's a genius.
I'm gonna have a doze.

33:10.096 --> 33:12.690
- Are we there?
- No, we're not. We're here.

33:12.799 --> 33:16.131
We're in the middle
of a fucking gale.

33:16.234 --> 33:18.794
You'll have to keep
a look out your side.

33:18.904 --> 33:21.737
If you see anything, tell me.
Get hold of that map.

33:21.840 --> 33:24.570
- Where's the whiskey?
- What for?

33:24.676 --> 33:27.236
I got a bastard
behind the eyes.

33:27.346 --> 33:30.144
I can't take aspirins
without a drink.

33:30.248 --> 33:33.148
- Where's the aspirins?
- Probably in the bathroom.

33:33.250 --> 33:36.947
We've come out here in the middle
of nowhere without aspirins?

33:37.054 --> 33:40.319
- Where are we?
- How should I know where we are?

33:40.424 --> 33:43.825
I feel like a pig
shat in my head.

33:43.928 --> 33:47.488
Get hold of that map and look
for a place called Crow Crag.

34:04.613 --> 34:08.447
There must and shall be aspirin.

34:09.752 --> 34:12.812
Give me the keys.
Get out of the way.

34:12.920 --> 34:16.618
If I don't get aspirin,
I shall die...

34:16.725 --> 34:20.626
here on this
fucking mountainside!

34:35.976 --> 34:38.274
Christ Almighty!

35:12.877 --> 35:15.107
<i>Monty.</i>

35:32.029 --> 35:36.898
- What are you doing?
- Sitting down to enjoy my holiday.

35:39.737 --> 35:43.035
Right. Now, we're gonna have to
approach this scientifically.

35:43.139 --> 35:45.937
First thing we've got to do
is get this fire alight.

35:46.042 --> 35:48.272
Then we split into two
fact-finding groups.

35:48.377 --> 35:50.811
I'll deal with the water
and other plumbing.

35:50.913 --> 35:53.575
You can check the fuel
and wood situation.

35:57.720 --> 36:00.620
- What's that?
- The fuel and wood situation.

36:00.722 --> 36:03.714
There's nothing out there
except a hurricane.

36:07.729 --> 36:10.857
- This place is uninhabitable.
- Give it a chance. It's got to warm up.

36:10.966 --> 36:14.060
Warm up? We may as well
sit around a cigarette.

36:14.169 --> 36:16.728
This is ridiculous.

36:16.837 --> 36:20.170
We'll be found dead
in here next spring.

36:21.408 --> 36:24.172
I've got a blinding
fucking headache.

36:24.278 --> 36:26.838
We must have heat.

36:30.084 --> 36:32.313
<i>We've got to keep
this bastard burning.</i>

36:32.418 --> 36:35.080
Well, we've got enough
furniture for tonight.

36:35.188 --> 36:38.089
Tomorrow we'll go down
that farm and get some logs.

36:38.191 --> 36:42.389
Mistake, I'm telling you.
This was a dreadful mistake.

38:53.418 --> 38:55.978
<i>- Who's there?
- Me.</i>

38:59.423 --> 39:01.323
What do you want?

39:01.425 --> 39:04.656
I'm a friend of Montague Withnail's.
He's lent us his cottage.

39:04.762 --> 39:09.222
I wondered if you could
sell us some food... eggs and things.

39:09.333 --> 39:11.893
Hmm?

39:14.038 --> 39:17.564
What about wood and coal?

39:17.674 --> 39:20.643
I'm not from London, you know.

39:20.743 --> 39:24.008
I don't care
where you come from!

39:24.113 --> 39:26.980
<i>Not the attitude
I'd been given to expect...</i>

39:27.083 --> 39:29.313
<i>from the H.E. Bates novel
I'd read.</i>

39:29.419 --> 39:34.151
<i>I thought they'd all be out the back,
drinking cider, discussing butter.</i>

39:34.256 --> 39:36.156
<i>Clearly a myth.</i>

39:36.258 --> 39:40.354
<i>Evidently, country people are no more
receptive to strangers than city dwellers.</i>

39:43.432 --> 39:47.334
Do you think you could tell me
where I could buy some coal and wood?

39:47.436 --> 39:50.563
<i>You'll have to see me son.
He runs this farm.</i>

39:50.671 --> 39:53.663
<i>- Where is your son?
- Up in top fields.</i>

39:53.774 --> 39:57.870
<i>You can't miss him.
His leg's bound in polythene.</i>

40:22.334 --> 40:25.735
Wake up, you bastard!
Wake up!

40:27.373 --> 40:30.706
Wake up, you bastard!
You gotta get wood.

40:32.644 --> 40:34.874
Jesus! You're covered in shit.

40:34.980 --> 40:36.880
I tried to get the fuel and wood.

40:36.982 --> 40:39.882
There's a miserable
little pensioner down there.

40:39.984 --> 40:42.714
- She wouldn't give it to me.
- Where are we gonna get it, then?

40:42.820 --> 40:45.118
There's a man on the mountain.

40:45.223 --> 40:48.750
Why he's up there fuck knows.

40:48.860 --> 40:51.590
But he's up there
with a leg in polythene.

40:51.696 --> 40:54.095
You can't miss him.
He's your man.

40:54.197 --> 40:56.893
And have another look
in that shed. Find anything.

40:57.000 --> 40:59.901
If you can't find anything,
bring in the shed.

41:04.341 --> 41:07.469
How come Monty owns
such a horrible little shack?

41:07.577 --> 41:09.511
No idea.

41:09.613 --> 41:12.172
You never discuss
your family, do you?

41:12.281 --> 41:15.079
I fail to see my family
as of any interest to you.

41:15.184 --> 41:17.744
I have absolutely
no interest in yours.

41:17.853 --> 41:21.482
I dislike relatives in general,
my own in particular.

41:21.590 --> 41:24.923
- Why?
- Because... I've told you why.

41:25.027 --> 41:28.985
We're incompatible.
They don't like me being on stage.

41:29.097 --> 41:31.759
<i>Then they must be delighted
with your career.</i>

41:31.866 --> 41:34.528
- What do you mean?
- You rarely are.

41:34.636 --> 41:36.831
You just wait!
Just you wait!

41:36.938 --> 41:39.998
When I strike, they
won't know what hit them.

41:40.108 --> 41:42.303
Tractor approaching.

41:42.410 --> 41:45.378
Now get after him.
That's the man.

41:47.848 --> 41:51.113
- Hey, stop!
- Stop!

41:51.218 --> 41:53.186
Stop! Please!

41:53.287 --> 41:55.983
Stop, please!
Please stop!

41:59.158 --> 42:01.854
Please stop!

42:01.961 --> 42:04.862
<i>- Are you the farmer?
- Shut up! I'll deal with this!</i>

42:04.964 --> 42:07.057
We've gone on holiday
by mistake.

42:07.166 --> 42:09.532
We're in this cottage here.
Are you the farmer?

42:09.635 --> 42:12.695
Stop saying that, Withnail!
Of course he's the fucking farmer!

42:12.805 --> 42:15.932
We're friends
of Montague Withnail.

42:16.041 --> 42:18.635
We desperately need
fuel and wood.

42:18.743 --> 42:22.042
Montague Withnail.
You must know him!

42:22.147 --> 42:24.308
Fat man, owns the cottage.

42:24.416 --> 42:27.317
I seen a fat man.
London type. Queer sort.

42:27.419 --> 42:29.649
Think his name's French, or summit.

42:29.754 --> 42:32.381
<i>- French?
- Aye. Adriene De La Touche.</i>

42:32.490 --> 42:35.050
He ain't been here
for a couple of years.

42:35.159 --> 42:38.458
- Last time I saw him he was with his son.
- Yeah, that's him.

42:38.562 --> 42:42.760
Listen, we're bona fide. We're not from
London. Could we have some fuel and wood?

42:42.867 --> 42:46.234
I could bring you some logs up later.
I've got the cows to feed first.

42:46.337 --> 42:48.770
- When?
- Shut up! That would be very kind.

42:48.872 --> 42:52.035
What about food? Do you think
you could sell us something to eat?

42:52.142 --> 42:55.111
I could bring you a chicken,
but you'll have to go to the village.

42:55.211 --> 42:57.270
- That would be very kind, Mr...
- Parkin.

42:57.380 --> 43:00.281
Mr. Parkin.
What happened to your leg?

43:00.383 --> 43:03.716
Got a randy bull up there.
Give me one in the knee.

43:17.332 --> 43:20.199
You wanna go out back?
Get some spuds up?

43:20.302 --> 43:24.032
Sorry, I can't.
My boots are in the oven.

43:24.138 --> 43:26.868
- You'd go if you had boots?

43:26.974 --> 43:28.965
<i>Gladly.</i>

43:54.233 --> 43:56.724
- I've got one!

44:22.393 --> 44:25.624
- Great. How much do we owe you?
- Pay us when you come down.

44:25.730 --> 44:27.993
- What about this chicken?
- He's on the back.

44:38.575 --> 44:41.510
With. With.

44:41.612 --> 44:44.705
Parkin's been.
There's our supper.

44:44.814 --> 44:47.612
- What are we supposed to do with that?
- Eat it.

44:47.717 --> 44:49.651
Eat it?
The fucker's alive.

44:49.752 --> 44:51.652
- Yeah, I know that. You've gotta kill it.
- Me?

44:51.754 --> 44:55.781
- I'm fire lighter and fuel collector.
- Yeah, I know that, but I got the logs in.

45:00.295 --> 45:02.991
It takes away your appetite
looking at it.

45:03.098 --> 45:05.589
No, it doesn't.
I'm starving.

45:05.700 --> 45:08.828
- How can we make it die?
- You have to throttle them.

45:08.937 --> 45:13.567
I think you should strangle it instantly,
in case it starts to make friends with us.

45:13.675 --> 45:17.440
All right, get hold of it.
You hold it down. I'll strangle it.

45:17.544 --> 45:21.605
I can't. Those dreadful, beady eyes.
They stare you out.

45:21.715 --> 45:25.583
It's a bloody chicken! Just think
of it with bacon across its back.

45:25.686 --> 45:28.211
All right,
I'll deal with this.

45:28.322 --> 45:30.882
You'll have to get
its guts out.

45:38.264 --> 45:41.392
Never point guns at people!
It's extremely dangerous.

45:41.501 --> 45:44.334
What about this roasting dish?
What are we gonna cook it in?

45:44.437 --> 45:48.168
You're the food and plumbings man. I have
no idea. I wish I'd found this an hour ago.

45:48.274 --> 45:51.037
I'd have taken great pleasure
in gunning this pullet down.

45:54.479 --> 45:57.505
- Shouldn't it be more bald than that?
- No, it shouldn't.

45:57.616 --> 46:02.212
Right. We're gonna
have to reverse the roles.

46:02.321 --> 46:06.518
We can bake the potatoes
in the oven...

46:06.624 --> 46:09.320
and we can boil
this bastard over the fire.

46:09.427 --> 46:12.191
- Let's get its feet off.
- No.

46:12.296 --> 46:14.787
It's gonna need its feet.

46:29.979 --> 46:32.709
It can stand with its legs
on either side of that.

46:40.189 --> 46:43.454
I've already put
two shilling pieces in.

46:43.559 --> 46:46.323
No, I haven't got another.

46:46.428 --> 46:49.727
It's not my fault
if the system doesn't work.

46:52.134 --> 46:54.499
The bitch hung up on me.

47:08.883 --> 47:11.851
<i>Hello? How are you?</i>

47:11.952 --> 47:14.614
Very well.

47:14.721 --> 47:19.090
A what? Why
wouldn't they see me?

47:19.192 --> 47:21.558
This is ridiculous.

47:21.661 --> 47:24.357
I haven't been up for a job
in three months!

47:24.464 --> 47:27.955
Understudy Constantine?
I'm not going to understudy Constantine.

47:28.067 --> 47:30.297
Why can't I play the part?

47:30.403 --> 47:32.633
This is ridiculous.

47:32.738 --> 47:35.605
No, I'm not in London.
Penrith.

47:35.708 --> 47:37.835
Penrith!

47:37.943 --> 47:39.968
Well, what about TV?

47:41.213 --> 47:43.976
Listen, I pay you
ten percent to do that.

47:44.082 --> 47:47.643
<i>Well, lick ten percent
of the asses for me, then!</i>

47:47.752 --> 47:50.482
<i>Hello? Hello? Hello?</i>

47:50.588 --> 47:55.150
Hello? How dare you?
Fuck you!

47:57.662 --> 48:02.462
<i>The bastard asked me to understudy
Constantine in The Seagull.</i>

48:04.802 --> 48:08.932
I don't want to understudy anybody,
especially that little pimp.

48:10.441 --> 48:13.035
Anyway, I loathe
those Russian plays.

48:13.143 --> 48:16.044
Always full of women
staring out of windows,

48:16.146 --> 48:18.204
whining about ducks
going to Moscow.

48:28.925 --> 48:31.553
What do you think
of Desmond Wolfe?

48:31.661 --> 48:34.788
- In respect of what?
- I'm thinking of changing my name.

48:34.896 --> 48:38.059
It's too like Donald Wolfit.

48:38.166 --> 48:40.191
Changeover point.

48:44.806 --> 48:47.366
- Think he's happier than us?
- No.

48:52.546 --> 48:54.673
I suppose happiness
is relative.

48:54.782 --> 48:57.512
I never thought it would be
a polythene bag without a hole in it.

48:57.618 --> 49:00.746
- Hey!
- What's the matter with him?

49:00.855 --> 49:04.188
- Shut the gate!
- You didn't shut the gate!

49:04.291 --> 49:06.281
<i>Stop that bull!</i>

49:08.127 --> 49:10.425
<i>Stop that bull!</i>

49:13.733 --> 49:16.793
Grab its ring!
Keep your bag up!

49:16.903 --> 49:19.269
<i>Out-mind him.</i>

49:19.372 --> 49:22.397
Hey, show no fear.
Just run at it.

49:22.508 --> 49:24.840
That can't be sensible, can it?
The bastard's about to run at me!

49:24.943 --> 49:27.241
- Well, he's randy!
- Yes, I know he is!

49:27.346 --> 49:29.644
Wants to get down there
and have sex with those cows.

49:29.748 --> 49:31.875
Shut up!

49:31.984 --> 49:36.080
- Run at it, shouting!
- Do as he says, start shouting.

49:38.489 --> 49:42.152
- He won't gore you.
- A coward you are, Withnail!

49:42.260 --> 49:45.491
An expert on bulls
you are not!

49:57.941 --> 49:59.841
Shut that gate
and keep it shut!

50:02.746 --> 50:05.647
I think an evening at the Crow.

50:08.418 --> 50:12.251
<i>If the Crow and Crown
ever had life, it was dead now.</i>

50:12.354 --> 50:14.879
<i>It was like
walking into a lung,</i>

50:14.990 --> 50:19.222
<i>a sulfer-stained, nicotine
yellow and fly-blown lung.</i>

50:19.328 --> 50:23.458
<i>Its landlord was a retired alcoholic
with military pretensions...</i>

50:23.566 --> 50:25.932
<i>and a complexion
like the inside of a teapot.</i>

50:26.936 --> 50:30.200
<i>By the time the doors opened,
he was arse-holed on rum...</i>

50:30.305 --> 50:32.432
<i>and got progressively
more arse-holed...</i>

50:32.540 --> 50:35.805
<i>till he could take no more</i>

50:38.746 --> 50:41.442
We'll have another pair
of large scotches.

50:59.099 --> 51:02.033
Thought I was going
for a minute.

51:02.134 --> 51:04.125
No man's put me down yet.

51:04.236 --> 51:06.329
Have you had any training
in the martial arts?

51:06.439 --> 51:08.839
Yes, as a matter of fact,
I have.

51:08.941 --> 51:11.808
Before I became a journalist,
I was in the Territorials.

51:11.911 --> 51:14.709
You know,
when you first came in,

51:14.814 --> 51:17.782
I knew you were a services man.

51:17.882 --> 51:21.340
You could never, never disguise it.

51:23.955 --> 51:27.186
- What were you in?
- Tanks.

51:27.292 --> 51:30.557
Africa Corps.
Little before your time.

51:30.662 --> 51:33.391
I don't suppose you've
engaged, have you?

51:33.497 --> 51:37.661
- Ireland.
- Ooh, crack at the Mick?

51:37.768 --> 51:40.703
We'll have another pair
of large scotches.

51:40.804 --> 51:43.364
These shall be my pleasure.

51:48.746 --> 51:50.713
What are you doing
up here, then?

51:50.813 --> 51:52.781
<i>We're doing
a feature for Country Life.</i>

51:52.882 --> 51:54.782
Survey of rural types.

51:54.884 --> 51:59.218
You know, farmers,
traveling tinkers,

51:59.322 --> 52:01.688
milkmen, that sort of thing.

52:01.791 --> 52:03.691
Have you...

52:06.194 --> 52:08.321
Have you metJake?

52:08.430 --> 52:10.990
Poacher.
Works the lake.

52:11.099 --> 52:14.626
But, uh, keep it
under your hat, hmm?

52:25.479 --> 52:27.572
What's all this army bollocks?

52:27.682 --> 52:30.310
We got a drink, didn't we?

52:33.054 --> 52:35.614
Time, gentlemen.

52:37.958 --> 52:39.948
I think he means it.

53:11.023 --> 53:14.116
- Go ask him if we can have one.
- What for?

53:14.225 --> 53:17.854
So we can eat it.
We're fed up with stew!

53:24.202 --> 53:27.194
Excuse me.
Could we have an eel?

53:27.305 --> 53:30.899
- You've got eels down your leg.
- You leave them alone.

53:31.007 --> 53:34.841
Nothing down there
of interest to you.

53:34.945 --> 53:37.709
Help us out, Raymond.

53:37.814 --> 53:41.978
These be fed
from asshole to beak.

53:43.820 --> 53:47.846
How about one of those pheasants?
Go on, ask him.

53:49.625 --> 53:53.391
Excuse me. We were wondering if we
could purchase a pheasant off of you?

53:53.496 --> 53:55.828
No. I've got nothing to sell.

53:55.931 --> 53:58.900
Come on, old boy.
What's in your hump?

53:59.001 --> 54:03.903
Now look, you. Them pheasants are
for his pot. These here are for my pot.

54:04.005 --> 54:06.940
<i>Now what makes you think I should
give you something for your pot?</i>

54:07.041 --> 54:09.805
- What pot?
- Our cooking pot.

54:09.911 --> 54:13.608
He knows. Hey, give us
a wheeze on that fag.

54:17.417 --> 54:20.853
I might come and see you lads in a week.
I might fetch you up a rabbit.

54:20.954 --> 54:23.718
We don't want a rabbit.
We want a pheasant.

54:23.824 --> 54:26.850
<i>Listen, you young prat.
I ain't got no pheasants.</i>

54:26.960 --> 54:29.485
I ain't got no birds,
no more than you have.

54:29.596 --> 54:32.724
Of course you have.
You're the poacher.

54:32.833 --> 54:35.824
If I hear more words
out of you,

54:35.935 --> 54:39.166
I'll put one of these here
black pods on you.

54:39.272 --> 54:42.332
- Don't threaten me with a dead fish.
- Half dead, he may be.

54:42.441 --> 54:46.104
But I'll come up after you,
and I'll wake you up with a live one.

54:46.212 --> 54:50.170
Sod your pheasants!
You'll have to find us first.

54:50.282 --> 54:53.115
<i>I know where you are,
at Crow Crag.</i>

54:53.218 --> 54:55.311
<i>I've been watching you.</i>

54:55.420 --> 54:58.184
Especially you,
prancing like a tit.

54:59.958 --> 55:02.756
You want working on, boy.

55:02.861 --> 55:06.660
If I see that silage heap
hanging about up here,

55:06.764 --> 55:09.995
I'll take the bastard
axe to him!

55:10.100 --> 55:14.002
Bastards!
You'll all suffer!

55:14.104 --> 55:16.572
I'll show the lot of you!

55:16.674 --> 55:20.110
I'm gonna be a star!

55:23.913 --> 55:26.006
Vegetables again.

55:26.082 --> 55:28.744
I'll be sprouting
bloody feelers soon.

55:28.852 --> 55:31.719
Must be 20,000 sheep
out there on those volcanoes,

55:31.821 --> 55:34.415
and we got a plate
full of carrots.

55:34.524 --> 55:37.891
- There's black puddings in it.
- Black puddings are no good to us.

55:37.994 --> 55:40.791
I want something's flesh!

55:52.374 --> 55:55.138
Look! Come here!
Down here. Look.

55:55.244 --> 55:57.973
Under the rock. I can see it.

55:59.213 --> 56:01.909
See him? Look.

56:02.016 --> 56:04.246
He's over there.
Look. Here.

56:04.352 --> 56:07.185
There's two of them here.
Look. Come on, come on.

56:07.288 --> 56:09.449
Where?

56:32.578 --> 56:35.775
I think I'll call myself
Donald Twain.

56:36.882 --> 56:41.012
Stop. Get down.

56:42.588 --> 56:45.055
It's him.
What does he want?

56:45.156 --> 56:48.523
- Go down there and ask him.
- Don't be a fool. He's got a gun.

56:48.626 --> 56:51.288
Bastard's psychotic.
You've only got to look at him.

57:01.605 --> 57:04.836
This place has become impossible.

57:04.942 --> 57:08.400
Perpetual rain, freezing cold.

57:08.512 --> 57:11.276
Now a bloody madman
on the prowl outside with eels.

57:11.381 --> 57:14.145
All right,
you made your point.

57:14.251 --> 57:17.413
We pack up.
We get out tomorrow.

57:17.520 --> 57:19.613
- What are you doing?
- I'm going for a slash.

57:19.722 --> 57:22.316
No, you're not. I can't get
my boots on when they're hot.

57:22.425 --> 57:25.155
- I'll go alone.
- You're not leaving me in here alone.

57:25.261 --> 57:28.822
<i>- Those are the kind of windows faces look in at.
- Then I won't have a slash.</i>

57:28.931 --> 57:31.161
And in both our interests, I think
we should sleep together tonight.

57:31.267 --> 57:34.326
Don't be ridiculous.
He's not gonna come up here in the dark.

57:34.436 --> 57:36.836
Of course he is.
If he catches one of us,

57:36.938 --> 57:39.668
he's got a better chance
of dealing with the other.

57:39.774 --> 57:42.368
<i>No.</i>

57:55.422 --> 57:58.789
What's the matter with you?
What are you laughing at?

57:58.892 --> 58:01.258
I was dreaming.
What do you want?

58:01.362 --> 58:04.820
You frightened the piss out of me.
Move over. I'm getting in.

58:09.369 --> 58:12.861
Oh, this is ridiculous.
I'll have to sleep in your bed.

58:12.972 --> 58:15.372
- I'll have to come with you.
- Will you get out?

58:15.475 --> 58:18.239
- No.
- All right, then I will.

58:26.685 --> 58:29.586
All right, you can stay,
but the gun doesn't.

58:29.688 --> 58:32.384
No. I have to keep the gun.
I intend to remain awake.

58:32.491 --> 58:35.085
- This is my bed, and I demand precedence.
- No!

58:40.831 --> 58:44.062
Mad fucking bastard!

59:06.723 --> 59:09.692
Shhh! Shhh!

59:09.793 --> 59:12.920
- Listen.
- There is nothing! Get to bed!

59:13.028 --> 59:15.428
I heard a noise.

59:15.531 --> 59:17.431
I must get in.

59:19.234 --> 59:22.692
<i>Oh, for fuck's sake.</i>

59:22.805 --> 59:25.000
- What was that?
- That's it. That's it.

59:25.107 --> 59:27.701
- What is it?
- It's the killer.

59:27.810 --> 59:31.768
<i>- It's probably foxes looking for grub.
- Listen. Listen.</i>

59:31.879 --> 59:34.609
Maybe it's the farmer.

59:34.715 --> 59:38.549
At 2:00 in the morning?
It's the killer.

59:38.653 --> 59:42.145
He's come to kill us.
What are we gonna do?

59:44.725 --> 59:47.659
He wants to come in.
He's trying to get in.

59:47.761 --> 59:50.753
He can't. He'll go away.

59:50.864 --> 59:52.957
He's going away.

59:58.338 --> 01:00:00.465
<i>This is all your fault.</i>

01:00:00.574 --> 01:00:03.542
You've even given him
the fucking gun.

01:00:08.447 --> 01:00:11.644
He's coming through the window.
He's getting in.

01:00:11.750 --> 01:00:14.913
- Give me the matches.
- Downstairs.

01:00:16.589 --> 01:00:21.150
He's in.
He's sharpening a fucking knife.

01:00:23.361 --> 01:00:26.762
We'll have to tackle him. You stay
in bed, pretending to be asleep.

01:00:26.865 --> 01:00:29.766
He'll go for you.
When he does, I'll jump on his back.

01:00:29.868 --> 01:00:32.803
No, no, no. It'll be too late.
I'll be knifed by then.

01:00:32.904 --> 01:00:35.736
We'll have to try
and make friends with him.

01:00:41.778 --> 01:00:45.145
They're going into your room.
It's you he wants.

01:00:45.249 --> 01:00:48.412
Offer him yourself.

01:00:59.162 --> 01:01:02.495
We mean no harm!

01:01:02.598 --> 01:01:06.932
<i>Oh, my boys!
My boys! Forgive me!</i>

01:01:07.035 --> 01:01:11.131
- Monty! Monty, Monty!
- Monty, you terrible cunt!

01:01:11.239 --> 01:01:14.470
<i>Forgive me. It was inconsiderate
of me not to have telegrammed.</i>

01:01:14.576 --> 01:01:17.568
What are you doing, prowling around
in the middle of the fucking night!

01:01:17.679 --> 01:01:21.615
I had a punctured tire.
I had to wait an eon for assistance.

01:01:21.716 --> 01:01:25.014
I'm sorry if I frightened you.
I should have knocked, but...

01:01:25.119 --> 01:01:29.112
<i>- I- I-I'll sleep in the other
room, if I may. - Anywhere you like.</i>

01:01:29.223 --> 01:01:32.715
Uh, yes, well.
Uh... good night.

01:01:36.897 --> 01:01:40.059
Brrr! Ah, good morning.
Did you sleep well?

01:01:40.166 --> 01:01:42.066
Mm-hmm.

01:01:46.639 --> 01:01:50.006
Um, I-I-I do apologize
for last night.

01:01:50.109 --> 01:01:54.011
- It was perfectly inconsiderate of me.
- It's perfectly all right, Monty.

01:01:54.113 --> 01:01:56.945
- You've been busy in here?
- As a bee.

01:01:57.049 --> 01:02:00.985
- How did you repair the window?
- Oh, I didn't break it.

01:02:01.086 --> 01:02:05.750
Merely forced it a little.
Sorry if I frightened you.

01:02:05.857 --> 01:02:08.951
There was an empty
wine bottle on the ledge.

01:02:09.061 --> 01:02:12.189
Oh, tomatoes. Yes.

01:02:17.835 --> 01:02:21.293
<i>Why don't you go and wake him?
Breakfast in 15 minutes.</i>

01:02:21.405 --> 01:02:25.739
The old order changeth,

01:02:25.843 --> 01:02:29.334
yielding place to new.

01:02:29.446 --> 01:02:34.179
And God fulfills Himself
in many ways.

01:02:34.284 --> 01:02:36.752
And soon...

01:02:37.854 --> 01:02:40.152
I suppose...

01:02:40.257 --> 01:02:42.350
I shall be swept away...

01:02:42.459 --> 01:02:45.757
by some vulgar little tumor.

01:02:47.229 --> 01:02:49.663
Oh, my boys.

01:02:49.765 --> 01:02:53.223
My boys,
we're at the end of an age.

01:02:53.335 --> 01:02:56.634
We live in a land
of weather forecasts...

01:02:56.739 --> 01:02:59.640
and breakfasts that 'set in,'

01:02:59.742 --> 01:03:03.677
shat on by Tories,
shoveled up by Labor.

01:03:03.778 --> 01:03:07.578
And here we are... we three...

01:03:07.682 --> 01:03:12.085
perhaps the last island
of beauty in the world.

01:03:15.189 --> 01:03:19.056
Now, which of you is going to be
a splendid fellow...

01:03:19.159 --> 01:03:22.151
and go down to the Rolls
for the rest of the wine?

01:03:22.262 --> 01:03:25.527
- I will.
- No, I'd better go. I wanna dig the car out anyway.

01:03:25.632 --> 01:03:29.398
- But we have my car, dear boy.
- Yes, but if it rains, we're buggered.

01:03:29.503 --> 01:03:31.835
- I mean...
- Stranded!

01:03:31.938 --> 01:03:35.429
- We'll leave the car till later. Leave this to me.
- I'll come. I fancy a walk.

01:03:35.541 --> 01:03:39.375
No, I hear you're a little wizard in the
kitchen. I shall need you, to work the joint.

01:03:39.478 --> 01:03:44.347
<i>- Yeah, you're the cook.
- And... what on earth are those?</i>

01:03:44.450 --> 01:03:46.782
- We forgot to bring our Wellingtons.
- Oh, but how dreadful.

01:03:46.886 --> 01:03:50.117
Do you mean you've been up here in all this
beastly mud and oomska without Wellingtons?

01:03:50.222 --> 01:03:53.019
Well, this afternoon
I shall take you both into Penrith...

01:03:53.124 --> 01:03:56.753
and get you fitted with some
good quality rubber boots.

01:04:00.365 --> 01:04:03.857
Garlic, rosemary and salt.

01:04:05.603 --> 01:04:08.594
I brought two of these in case either
of you was any good in the kitchen.

01:04:08.706 --> 01:04:11.971
- I'm not.
- Of course you are. Cooking is one of the natural instincts.

01:04:12.076 --> 01:04:15.807
Listen, Monty.
This is all very kind of you,

01:04:15.913 --> 01:04:18.381
but I really think I ought to be
out there getting work done on the car.

01:04:18.482 --> 01:04:21.076
You haven't time.
We're taking late luncheon at 3:00.

01:04:21.185 --> 01:04:24.244
- I'm afraid we have to leave by 3:00, Monty.
- Leave?

01:04:24.354 --> 01:04:27.221
Oh, didn't he tell you?
We have to get back to sign on.

01:04:27.323 --> 01:04:32.818
- Sign on? At the Labor Exchange?
- Yeah.

01:04:32.929 --> 01:04:37.298
It's sort of fashionable, actually.
All the actors do it. Even Redgrave.

01:04:38.968 --> 01:04:43.336
But surely you could forego
for just this one occasion.

01:04:43.438 --> 01:04:46.271
I've come a very long way
to see you both.

01:04:46.375 --> 01:04:51.312
<i>Can't, actually. I mean, I'd love to stay,
but he's more adamant to get back than I am.</i>

01:04:51.413 --> 01:04:54.541
Then we must choose
our moment...

01:04:56.784 --> 01:05:00.049
and have a word with him.

01:05:02.656 --> 01:05:05.420
I'm sure together
we could persuade him.

01:05:07.995 --> 01:05:11.487
There. Now, garlic,

01:05:11.599 --> 01:05:14.260
rosemary and salt.

01:05:14.367 --> 01:05:17.564
I can never touch meat
until it's cooked.

01:05:17.670 --> 01:05:20.935
As a youth, I used to weep
in butcher shops.

01:05:21.040 --> 01:05:24.203
<i>- I can't find the rosemary.
- Ah.</i>

01:05:26.279 --> 01:05:29.146
Can't find the rosemary.

01:05:30.816 --> 01:05:32.784
I'm sure we could find it
together.

01:05:35.687 --> 01:05:38.781
- Perhaps it's in the other bag.
- Perhaps it is.

01:05:38.891 --> 01:05:40.791
Shall we look?

01:05:44.630 --> 01:05:47.154
Oh, sorry. Sherry's in there.

01:05:52.637 --> 01:05:55.697
What do you mean, "sorry"? What's
going on? What's he doing here?

01:05:55.807 --> 01:05:58.071
We can't stay.
He won't leave me alone.

01:05:58.176 --> 01:06:00.576
<i>All right. We'll get the lunch done,
and then we'll leave.</i>

01:06:02.312 --> 01:06:05.873
I'm afraid
we must drink from these.

01:06:10.954 --> 01:06:14.219
I trust their shapes
will not offend your palates.

01:06:14.324 --> 01:06:18.726
- Chin-chin.
- To a delightful weekend in the country.

01:06:43.251 --> 01:06:45.583
I do think you could have shaved.

01:06:45.687 --> 01:06:48.781
What on earth will people
think of me turning up with you two?

01:06:48.890 --> 01:06:51.188
You look like a pair
of farm hands.

01:06:57.264 --> 01:06:59.164
Tsk!

01:06:59.266 --> 01:07:01.166
This is most embarrassing.

01:07:03.403 --> 01:07:05.871
Get away from the car.

01:07:05.973 --> 01:07:08.873
Buy the Wellingtons.

01:07:08.975 --> 01:07:12.376
I'm going to buy some razors
and shaving soap.

01:07:12.478 --> 01:07:15.242
I'll see you over there
in half an hour.

01:07:15.348 --> 01:07:18.249
- Pair of blues.
- One each.

01:07:19.752 --> 01:07:22.220
- I think a drink, don't you?
- What about the Wellingtons?

01:07:22.321 --> 01:07:24.220
Oh, bollocks
to the Wellingtons.

